response.Q0: I tried to click in as few nodes as possible until I found a satisfactory score. I tried to click first at intersection points, to discard (or choose) larger areas of the web.
response.Q1: At first I clicked close to the starting point, but then I realised that the value of the nodes was much larger (also in negative value) at the farthest points of the web. So then I tried to click at the last intersection points, in order to choose the best path and finally I clicked an all three final points from the last intersection point, to find the node which had the largest value.
response.Q2: It was difficult to see the value of my current points going down as I clicked on the nodes. So at first it prevented me from searching for nodes with the largest values, because I didn't want to pay too much "clicking fees". But since the nodes furthest away had rather high values, it was worth trying to find the best path at the cost of clicking more.
